#A
AC "ARMOR CLASS" "ARMOUR CLASS"

"AC" is your armor class.  It is a number from -100 to 100, roughly

  100 Naked person "Don't look!"
    0 Rather well armored (Plate mail, shields, protective gear around) 
 -100 Armored battle tank

The score command displays your armor class as a number such as 78;
this means 78 on a scale from -100 to 100.  That's not very good btw.

See also: SCORE
#
"SPELL ACID BLAST" "ACID BLAST"

Usage       : cast 'acid blast' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

With acid blast, the caster shoots a solid stream of acid that, if it hits,
scorches the victim horribly.  The damage done by acid blast is dependent on
the level of the caster.

See Also: -
#
ADVENTURE CITY STRUCTURE TRAVEL

(Adventure) (City) (Structure) and (Travel) refer to the purpose of a zone
in the mud.
Cities are zones where you aren't overwhelmed by agressive mobs, where there
are shops to buy things, and where there is usually a place to rent out.
Travel zones are routes of connection between generally cities.
Adventure zones are places where agressive mobs, good equipment, good
experience and good gold can be had.
Structure zones are Adventure zones that are set indoors.
A list of zones can be had by typing 'areas'.

See Also: AREAS
#
"SPELL AERIAL SERVANT"
Usage       : cast 'aerial servant'
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Aerial servant summons a weak flying servant to do your bidding.

See also: FOLLOW, ORDER
#
AGE

Age is measured in mud days where a mud day is 36 minutes real time. As your 
character ages, they regenerate mana and hit points more quickly. Look for
items that add to your age or just play the mud for a long time and you'll
really notice the bonus.

See also: -
#
"SPELL AID"

Usage       : cast 'aid' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : 40

Imbues the victim with supernatural presence, increasing hit points and
damage done to enemies.

See Also: BLESS, DAMROLL
#
"SPELL AIR ELEMENTAL" "SPELL EARTH ELEMENTAL" "SPELL FIRE ELEMENTAL" "SPELL WATER ELEMENTAL"

Usage:        cast '[air|earth|fire|water] elemental'
Accumulative: -
Duration:     Instantaneous

These four druid spells summon elementals from other planes of existence
to do the bidding of the caster.  Each type of elemental has its own
unique strengths and weaknesses.  The druid with low charisma should
beware, for the elementals do not come willingly, and they will attack
if not suitably impressed with your power.

See Also: -
#
ALIAS ALIASES ALIAS

An alias is a single command used to represent one or more other commands.
The ALIAS command can be used to manipulate your character's aliases.  Type
ALIAS alone to see a list of your currently defined aliases.

> alias

Type ALIAS <alias name> <command> to create a new alias.  The alias name must
be one word.  The command can be any string.  Aliases may not be nested or
used recursively.  Any command may be overriden by an alias (other than the
ALIAS command itself, of course).

> alias gbb get bread bag
> alias gac get all corpse

^G*^nType ALIAS <alias-name> to DELETE an alias that has already been
defined.^G*^n

> alias gbb

A semicolon (";") can be used to define multiple actions to be taken with
a single alias.

> alias eat get bread bag; eat bread

Note that the 'eat' contained within the eat alias is interpreted as the MUD's
internal eat command; aliases may not be nested or used recursively.  The
variables $1, $2, ... $9 may be used to represent arguments given with
an alias.  For example:

> alias killem cast 'fireball' $1; cast 'harm' $2
> killem fido mage

Would cast fireball on fido, followed by casting harm on mage.  Variables
may be used repeatedly and in any order:

> alias helpem cast 'heal' $1; cast 'bless' $1; cast 'armor' $1

The special variable $* represents the entire input line after an alias:

> alias tr tell rasmussen $*
> tr hi there, how are you today?
You tell Rasmussen, 'hi there, how are you today?'

See also: 
#
ALIGNMENT GOOD EVIL NEUTRAL

Alignment in the game can be very important!  Some mobs attack you based on
whether you are good or evil or neutral!  Alignment varies from 1000 (saintly)
to -1000 (satanic).  Good ranges from 1000 to 351, neutral from 350 to -350,
and evil from -351 down to -1000.  Whenever you kill a mobile, you move closer
to their alignment based on your level vs. their level.

For example: You find that you are suddenly zapped by a sword thats evil only.
You've gotta become evil again!!  ... you check 'score' and see that your
alignment has become -324.  Why, just go kill some good creatures, something
at least of alignment 400, and you'll be evil again. >:-> Simple no?

See also: SCORE, DETECT ALIGNMENT
#
ALL

'all' is used to refer to objects so that you can do fun things like
> get all
(to pick up all the items in the room)
> get all.bread
(to get all the bread in the room)

and so on.

As a side note, you can type get 2.bread to pick up the 2nd bread in the room.
Sometimes that's a handy way to get and drop specific items that have the 
same keywords.

See Also: -
#
ANSI COLORS COLOURS

If you have a color-capable terminal, you may enable useful color-coding
of information with the COLOR sommand, and you may also color phrases
for fun with ^^ (caret).

>>NOTE<<
Placing a ^^n at the end of a colored phrase is STRONGLY recommended to
preserve the integrity of the color stack and to prevent "bleeding colors".
If you bleed color in your title, you may be notitled until you understand
how much this annoys other players.
>>NOTE<<

Usage for color command: color <field> <color>

Colors available:
^nnormal^n		^rred^n		^ggreen^n		^yyellow^n
^bblue^n		^mmagenta^n		^ccyan^n		^wwhite^n
		^Rbright red^n	^Gbright green^n	^Ybright yellow^n
^Bbright blue^n	^Mbright magenta^n	^Cbright cyan^n	^Wbright white^n

Color without any argument shows your color-coding status.
Color on enables color-coding, color off disables color-coding.

Usage for color-coding phrases: ^^<color><phrase>^^n

<color> is the first-letter abbreviation of one of the available colors;
for bold/bright colors, it is the uppercase first-letter abbreviation.

^^^^ outputs as a single caret if it is ever necessary.

See Also: TOGGLE
#
"SPELL ANIMATE DEAD"
Usage       : cast 'animate dead' corpse
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell turns a corpse into a mindless undead servant. There are many kinds
of undead servants and the more powerful you are, the greater the power of
your undead minions (generally).

