#
"AREA SPELLS" "AREA AFFECT"

Area affect spells blast everything in the target's room that isn't charmed
to the caster or grouped with him.  Good examples of area affect spells can
be found in: burning hands, fireball, and earthquake but there are many of
them. You have to be a little careful with area affect spells and generally
only use them on groups of mobs if you are *sure* that you can kill them all
when they attack you.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL ARMOR" "SPELL ARMOUR"

Usage       : cast 'armor' <victim> 
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 24 Hours

The Armor spell will improve your AC by 2, or -20 in the 100 to -100 scale.

See Also: AC
#
ASSIST

Usage: ASSIST <person in need>

If Quifael is being beaten senseless by a warg and you feel brave enough
to help him, type ASSIST QUIFAEL to hit the warg.  Note that the warg will
keep hitting Quifael; assist only makes you start to fight whomever you're
trying to assist.

> assist quifael

See also: RESCUE, FLEE
#
ATTRIBUTES STRENGTH INTELLIGENCE WISDOM DEXTERITY CONSTITUTION CHARISMA

There is an "score" command that after 9th level lets you see your 
attributes.  In general though, you don't need this command to really tell
what they are (roughly).  Here's some guidelines for the major attributes,
what they're good for, and how to tell if you have good stats:

Attribute	Good for?	
---------	---------
Strength	+hit, +dam
Intelligence	mage spell success
Wisdom		cleric spell success
Dexterity	# attacks/rnd,+hit,+ac,ability to flee
Constitution	+hit points
Charisma	bard spell success, number of followers

See Also: -
#
AUCTIONS CHANNELS CSAY GOSSIP GRATS NOAUCTION NOGOSSIP NOGRATS
These are channels reserved for specific purposes.  Messages on these
channels reach everyone who is monitoring them.  You must be at least level
three to use these channels.

auction:
Usage: auction <item> <starting bid>
       auction [STAT|IDENTIFY]
       auction [STOP|CANCEL]
       auction TALK <message>
       auctalk <message>
       bid <amount>

gossip <string>
grats <string>

> gossip Hey, is that a short sword on your belt or are you happy to see me?
> grats LEVEL!!!!!!!!
> grats GRATS!!!!!!!

See also: SAY, GSAY, NOREPEAT
#
AUTO

There are a whole series of auto-toggles: Autoassist, Autodirs, Autoexits,
Autogold, Autoloot, Autosacrifice, and Autosplit (so far). Whether a
particular auto-feature is on or off can be seen with the "toggle" command.

See also: AUTOASSIST, AUTODIRS, AUTOEX, AUTOGOLD, AUTOLOOT, AUTOSAC,
          AUTOSPLIT, TOGGLE, AUTOSCAN, BATTLEBRIEF
#
AUTOASSIST "AUTO ASSIST"

Use this auto-feature if you would like to assist anyone in your group who
starts fighting. A great feature if you are a little lagged or dont have a
snazzy client.

See also: AUTO
#
AUTODIRS "AUTO DIRS"

This gives you a nice brief listing of the nearby exits. The format looks
something like: { N E S U } on one line, with your prompt on the next.
Its almost too brief though because its so easy to accidentally walk into
a deathtrap with it.  Autoexits is more complete and shows you doornames 
too.

See also: AUTO, AUTOEXITS
#
AUTOEXITS "AUTO EXITS"

Autoexits gives you a complete list (well fairly, heh) of all the exits 
out of the room you are in. It's just like typing "exits" each time you 
look in a room. It can be a little spammy but it's really good an helping
you orient yourself and avoiding deathtraps by name.

See also: AUTO, AUTODIRS
#
AUTOGOLD "AUTO GOLD"

Autogold sets things up so that if you kill a mob you immediately take the
gold from the corpse. Of course you have to be able to see the corpse to
take the gold from it; details, details ...

See also: AUTO
#
AUTOLOOT "AUTO LOOT"

Autoloot sets things up so that if you kill a mob, you loot its corpse. Its
like an instant version of "get all corpse", so fast that even people with
smart clients can't possibly take the equipment you fought so hard for.

See also: AUTO
#
AUTOREPORT "AUTO REPORT"

Autoreport is used by clerics and other members of groups to watch the
status of other group members during a fight. The report is automatically
displayed after every round of combat. If you have a slow connection or
don't like the spam, keep this disabled.

See also: AUTO, Toggle
#
AUTOSACRIFICE "AUTO SACRIFICE"

Autosac as it is more commonly called, sacrifices the corpse of a mob right
after you slay it, but not before you've had a chance to take its gold and
loot it for equipment (assuming you have toggled either one on) One note of
caution - if your inventory is loaded down to the point where you can no
longer really loot, and autosac is on, autosac will junk the corpse and
everything in it, so BEWARE! You might *accidentally* junk the best equipment
in the mud, *right after* you and others fought hard for it. Watch out!
Know what you're doing when you autosac!

See also: AUTO
#
AUTOSCAN "AUTO SCAN"

Autoscan is used to automatically scan surrounding rooms when you move
or use the look command.

See also: AUTO, TOGGLE
#
AUTOSPLIT "AUTO SPLIT"

Autosplit is a great command for someone who is grouping and to be useful,
pretty much requires that autogold be toggled on. Autosplit makes you split
the gold you get from mobs when they die.

See also: AUTO, AUTOGOLD
#
AWARE

Mobs that are "aware" can't be backstabbed!  Neither can mobs (and players)
who are affected by the ESP spell.  Dang, poor thieves have it rough.

See also: ESP
#
AWAY AFK

Usage     : away

Sets an (AWAY) flag in your title to let others know you're 
away from the keyboard "AFK". They will be informed on if they 
attempt to "TELL" you or by typing the command "WHO".

See also: -
#B
BACKSTAB BS

Thief and Bard only.

Backstab is a way to sneak up on a person and attempt to place your dagger
in his back, at exactly the point where it does most damage.  A successful
backstab gives a damage multiplier, depending on level.

The chance of successfully backstabbing depends on your stats. You can 
always backstab sleeping people.

See also: -
#
BANK WITHDRAW DEPOSIT BALANCE "BALANCE SHEET"
Commands to take money out of the bank, put money in the bank, or see how
much money you have in the bank.  Can be used at any branch of the First
National Bank of CircleMUD (wherever you see an automatic teller machine).

> deposit 400
> withdraw 1000
> balance

See also: -
