#
"SPELL BARKSKIN"

Usage       : cast 'barkskin' <self>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 24

This spell causes the caster's skin to take on the rough texture of bark, 
reducing the likelihood of being struck in combat.

See Also: ARMOR
# 
BASH

Fighter and Bard only.

The success of a bash depends upon how well you are learned. To bash someone
is to attempt to 'knock' that person over. If you succeed you will inflict
minor damage, and cause the target to fall on it's rear. The target will be
sitting, and will take 1.5 times damage.  They will get up about 4 hits
after they are bashed. A bash makes you unable to type commands for 2 
rounds.  It is important to note that if you miss your bash, you will fall
and recieve 1.5 times damage until you stand, just as if you had been
bashed.

See Also: RESCUE, KICK
#
BATTLE

Usage: battle

Battle takes you to the playerkilling arena.  In the arena you wont lose
your equipment if you die; your corpse always goes back to the temple.

See Also: DEATHMATCH
#
BATTLEBRIEF

Usage: battlebrief

Is the toggle to enable seeing yours and/or others battle messages.

See Also: TOGGLE
#
"SPELL BATTLE HYMN"

Usage       : cast 'battle hymn'
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Level Dependent

Battle hymn casts inspire on an entire group.

See Also: INSPIRE
#
BERSERK

Warrior skill that allows them to hit every mob in the room once for one
round, and costs 10 movement points, and keeps you from doing anything else
for one round of 'Violence'.

See Also: -
#
BITE

Undead only.
Usage: bite <victim>

Bite is an innate skill of the undead to relieve their thirst for blood.
If the undead is much more powerful than the bitten victim, they can even
replenish their hit points with the lifeblood of their victim.

See Also: - 
#
"SPELL BLESS"

Usage       : cast 'bless' <victim | object>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 6 Hours, permanent for objects.

Bless on a target PC or NPC will improve the target's saving throw versus spells
and improve the hitroll depending on the level of the caster.

Bless on an item currently has no defined action. It is only possible
to bless non-evil items, and the object blessed may weight no more
than five pounds per level of caster. 

See Also: AID, HITROLL 
#
"SPELL BLINDNESS"

Usage       : cast 'blindness' <victim>
Accumulative: No.
Duration    : 2 hours.

Blindness will blind a victim failing its saving throw.
A blinded person will have -4 penalty to both hi
troll and AC.

See Also: AC
#
BLOCK

Block is a fighter/bard skill that allows the player to block the attacks of
the mob they're fighting for one round. Very handy skill.

See Also: BASH
#
BOARD DISEMBARK SHIP STEER

Ships are full-fledged areas that can also be moved through other areas
like a vehicle.  Players generally board ship, steer around (where is
that tiller anyway?), beat up a few mobs while aboard, and disembark
onto a suitably dry land.

See Also: -
#
BOTS ROBOT

Bots are scripts that are run on a player's Mud client.  Bots will no
longer be permitted here if the player is afk, and any player found using
a bot can be frozen, disconnected, have eq or level stripped, or simply
be warned.

See Also: TWINK
#
"BULLETIN BOARDS" BOARDS

Bulletin boards are the forum of interplayer communication on the MUD.
There are different bulletin boards for different purposes -- for example,
a standard mortal board, a board for immortals, a board for fun "social"
messages, etc.  Naturally, not all players may be allowed to read all
types of boards.

Type "LOOK BOARD" to see the messages already posted on a board.  Type
"WRITE <subject>" to post a message to a board; terminate a message with
a '@' as the first character on a line.  Type "READ <number>" to read a
post.  Type "REMOVE <number>" to remove your own messages.

> look at board
> write Am I using these boards correctly?
[writes the message; terminates with a '@']
> look at board
> read 6
> remove 6

See Also: -
#
BRIEF

Toggle "brief mode".  When in brief mode, you don't see the descriptions of
the room you are in; only the name of the room and the people and objects
there.  Unless you're very familiar with the area in which you're travelling,
however, it is not advisable to use this command.  Frequently, you will find
small but vital hints in the descriptions of the rooms: An extra peek at your
surroundings could mean the difference between life and death!

If you explicitly type 'look', you will always see the full room description,
even in BRIEF mode.

See Also: COMPACT, LOOK
#
BUG TYPO IDEA

For making useful suggestions to the Powers that Be.

{bug | typo | idea} <text>

> bug the entire game crashes when I type 'put bag in bag'
> idea make a restaurant in Kore
> typo 'sence' should be spelled 'sense'

See Also: -
#
BUGBEAR

Bugbears are giant relatives of goblins that only value two things in life,
survival and treasure. Typically they eat what they hunt, with *anything*
being fair game. They are fierce in battle, yet not very intelligent, and
since they can see in the dark they prefer to live either underground or in
caves.

See Also: RACE
#
BUILDERS

Here on Heroes of Kore we're always looking for more builders and more areas.
If you have an idea or suggestion, you can jot it down with the "idea" command.
But if you feel that creative urge, why not grab ahold of one of the
Implementors and talk over your idea with them? They are usually pretty busy,
but sometimes an area idea will really catch their interest. Kore has a strong
medieval/fantasy theme and area ideas that feature very difficult mobs and
great rewards are perfect.

See Also: - 
#
BUILDING-STANDARDS

- Graph paper is your friend. You should always map out your areas prior to
  building.
- Never refer to a mob or removable object in the room desc. It looks silly
  if the mob or object isn't there.
- Never refer to the time of day, time passes quickly on a mud.
- Never assume a player is coming from a certain direction.
- Use your extras! If you refer to anything in the desc that is not a object
  that loads in the room, make a extra for it.
- Formatting and indenting is a must for room and mob desc. Depending on the
  size of the desc , objects desc should also be.
- Room length should be atleast three lines long and no more then nine long.
- Don't tell a char what he feels emotionally. IE You are scaried. A better
  way to say it would be - The dark and foggy atmosphere is chilling and
  would scare even the most stalwart of adventurers.
- Never ever start a room desc off with YOU. Never Never Never No Never. 
  Try to limit your use of the word YOU. <--- Ayana don't like that!
- Areas should be unique and follow the theme of the mud. Never steal a area
  from another mud.
- It should be possible to map your area on paper with a minimal confusion.
- Room names should be capitalized properly. First letter of any room name
  is capitalized no matter what. Capitalized each of the following words
  unless they are unimportant like "a" "of" "the".
- Don't tell the person exactly what room they are in unless it is apparent
  from the desc. Rather then "King Karns Bedroom" say A Royal Bedroom.
- Mobs must have desc.
- Objects must have extra desc.
- Gold on mobs should be set at 0 as it will automatically generated.
- All mobs should be flaged stay zone so they don't leave the zone.
- Any toys found in your zone will be changed. (over powered weapons and
  objects)

Above is subject to change etc... If you see a need to do something that
should not be done etc... Ask approval prior to doing.

See Also - 
#
"SPELL BURNING HANDS"

Usage       : cast 'burning hands' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Level       : Level 5 magic user.
Save        : Versus spell for half damage.

This spell is not very powerful but attacks all mobs in a room.

See Also: - 
#
BURY

Bury is just like sacrifice, only with different messages. You receive 5 coins
for every corpse you bury. You may want to set autosacrifice on if you kill
things a lot. ;)

See Also: AUTOSACRIFICE
#
BUY

If you'd like to purchase an item from a shop and have the money, you can buy
it.  Items can be bought by name, or by their number in the shop listing,
and can be bought in quantity.
 
Examples:
 
> buy sword        (buy the first sword on the list)
> buy #3           (buy the third item on the list)
> buy 4.sword      (buy the fourth sword on the list)
> buy 10 bread     (buy 10 pieces of bread)
> buy 10 #2        (buy 10 of the second item on the list)
 
See Also: SHOPS, SELL, LIST, VALUE
#C
"SPELL CALL LIGHTNING"

Usage       : cast 'call lightning' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Save        : Versus spell for half damage.

This spell will use the "force of nature" to make a lightning
strike the victim. It is therefore only possible to call lightning
outside, and it has to be raining (or worse).

The lightning will inflict (level)d8 points of damage, up to a
maximum of 15d8 damage points.

See Also: WEATHER, CONTROL WEATHER
#
CAST CASTING

For "magical" people. If you want to throw a spell at someone or something.
Example : cast 'burning hands' <player>
   Note that the name of the spell must be enclosed by "'"s.

See also : help on each individual spell, for example:
  > help cure ligh
  > help ventri
  > help energy drain

See Also: -
#
CHANGES

10/19/01 - Fixed bug in stock Circle code that caused you to lose
	   gold when you died while linkdead.
10/11/01 - Gnomes and Hobbits can now be warriors.  Thanks to
	   Thanatos for this suggestion.
04/15/01 - Hostile affect spells will now trigger combat.  This
           is basically anything that can be cast in combat.
04/15/01 - Faerie fire made hostile.
04/13/01 - I have TEMPORARILY removed my previous change to
           damroll.  The effects were too chaotic, so I'm going
           to work on another solution.
04/13/01 - Turns out acid blast was doing much more consistent
           damage than say, color spray and word of death.  I
           took the same formula used for acid blast and modified
           it to work with these spells, so their damage should
           be more consistent.
04/13/01 - Any clan member who is above CLAN_LVL_MEMBER may now
           initiate new members.  Only the clan leader may
           outcast or set clan levels.
04/13/01 - Implemented Jeshko's suggestion on languages.  To
           understand a language is no longer based on race, but
           on the language itself, so halfelves can now understand
           elves, etc.
04/09/01 - I'm in the process of adding affects to what you
           see when you look 'at' someone.  It might get a bit
           spammy, if so use 'diagnose' to see someone.
04/09/01 - Took out the ranged slot.  Nothing will be replacing
           it, and you can junk the bows for all I care.
04/09/01 - Bug in bash and trip fixed.  Bad position check.
04/07/01 - In the process of changing some equipment and progs.
           Just FYI really, not going to take complaints on eq
           changes.
04/07/01 - Weapons with damage spells on them have lost them.  Some
           might come back, but under different rules and toned down.
04/06/01 - Beginning the long process of balancing spells across
           classes.  This is going to make spell damage a bit more
           random.  Potential damage won't change much, but average
           will fluctuate.  This corresponds with the earlier change
           to melee classes.
04/06/01 - Changed the cost for mana shell in the code.  You will
           now be charged mana for base damage before damage is
           modified by sanc, etc.
04/06/01 - Added mana shell.
04/06/01 - Ranged combat has been completely removed from the game.
04/06/01 - Melee damage has been modified somewhat to make damage
           a bit more random, and a bit more based on average
           damage of the weapon.
04/06/01 - Added fireshield.
04/06/01 - Mob saving throws lowered very slightly.
04/06/01 - Web recoded and re-added, now mage only.
04/04/01 - Trip and Bash both now have verbose messages.
04/01/01 - Trip now more effective vs. players.
04/01/01 - Stoneskin and mirror image now actually work vs. bash.
           In addition you no longer need a weapon to bash, you
           need a shield.  Much more logical.
04/01/01 - MAX_ALIAS for any level is now 100
01/14/01 - Doubled the number of possible affects in the mud, and
	   probably added some new bugs.  But hey, we needed some.

See Also: OLDCHANGES
