11/19/00 - Bug in stand that allowed you to stand in combat after
	   having been bashed or tripped and were then able to
	   cast non-combat spells.
09/25/00 - Initiate should be fixed.
09/22/00 - Clan members ranked lvl 2 can now initiate new members.
07/09/00 - Quest objects are now no locate.
04/13/00 - Kore has changed, some of you may recognize it.  Expect
	   the city to change quite a bit in the coming days.
04/08/00 - Read the updated helpfile for DEATHMATCH
03/27/00 - Took out several of the ways charm person can fail.
03/27/00 - Quickdraw is being redone.  For the time being you
	   will not get any attacks from quickdraw, it will
	   still make you stand and wield a weapon.
03/27/00 - Rewrote most of critical hit, see necessary helpfiles
	   for changes.
03/27/00 - Fixed the damage message for critical hits.
03/27/00 - Mob regen has been slightly modified again.
03/27/00 - Saving throws are now visible in score if you're level
	   25 or higher.
03/27/00 - Charm may no longer be cast in combat.  What's with that
	   anyway?
03/27/00 - Curse may now be cast in combat.
03/27/00 - Attempting to charm a mob (and failing) is considered an
	   act of aggression.  Also, when mobs are free of your charm
	   they may choose to exact revenge.
03/26/00 - Curse will now affect the target's saving throws.  I know
	   you liked that minus 1 to their hitroll, but this might
	   be more effective.
03/26/00 - Charmed mobs will now keep fighting, but they might not like
	   you so much if you leave them.
03/26/00 - No more multiple backstabs and circles.  I know, I know, I've
	   finally gone and ruined the mud.  Even Knife hates me.  Oh the
	   humanity!
03/26/00 - You should get exp when charmies get a kill if they're grouped
	   again.
03/26/00 - Fixed the age-old phantom damage bug in ranged combat.  Should
	   also take care of the weird messages when a mob enters the room.
03/26/00 - A lot of the combat skills are having the damage they do tweaked.
	   Most were poorly written and didn't take into account damroll
	   and other factors.
03/26/00 - Re-scaled the damage messages.  Tweak Tweak.
03/26/00 - Spell damage has been changed.  Spells used to do more damage to
	   mobs.  That is no longer true.  Please refer all complaining
	   to /dev/null.  Thank you, drive through.
03/26/00 - Fixed problem where you'd see mpdamage.  Also changed it so you're
	   not doing mpdamage to yourself.  You'll also no longer get damage
	   exp for mpdamage and poison damage, and you won't gain exp for
	   dying to poison or mpdamage.
03/26/00 - Fixed the broken idea board.
03/26/00 - You can no longer yank in combat.  Bad men.
03/26/00 - Added a message to retreat that will show you which direction
	   you take when you leave combat if you successfully retreat.
03/26/00 - Damage messages have been recoded, yay.  Ok, so there are some
	   bugs, but it kinda rules.
03/24/00 - Class experience has been tweaked.  Some of the class experience
	   modifiers were changed.  Thieves and druids were made a bit easier
	   to level while clerics were made a bit more difficult.  This is 
	   part of an effort to maintain class balance when remort classes
	   are available.
03/24/00 - Mob regen has been lowered somewhat.
03/24/00 - Removed 40 or so unopened zones.  This should make quests a lot
	   more consistent and cut down on mem usage of the mud.
03/24/00 - Added a 'clanleave' command.  This will make you an outcast.  Do
	   not use hastily, as we will not reverse this if you change your
	   mind.
03/24/00 - Mobs should no longer die on the pulse while you're fighting them.
03/24/00 - Fixed some problems with shops, still working on getting these right.
03/20/00 - Berserk now has a 2 round delay.  It was always supposed to, dunno
	   why it was overlooked.
- Regen has been moved from the tick and placed on the pulse.  This may
require some tweaking over the next few days.
- Delete has been re-enabled.  If you delete your character we will never
ever restore it.
- There is a new zone flag for active zones.  If you get into an inactive
zone, you'll be told you shouldn't be there.
- You can now customize your prompt. See 'help custprompt' for details.
- Players can now supply an email address in case of password problems.
  See 'help email'.
- Poofins and Poofouts now save when you rent
- Titles will now be given out by gods level 58 and above only.
- Thri-kreen wear_face is fixed.  Thanks for pointing this
out Fei.
- Power Word Stun now gets a save.
- There is now a high rate of failure when trying to summon 
someone who is fighting.
- Backstabbing while stoneskinned will now halve your chance
for extra attacks.
- Helper mobs will now assist mobs vs. mobs.
- Players who are set noauction will no longer hear auctalk.
thanks Cameron.
- Fixed "worn on face" for thri-kreen.  Thanks Fei for pointing
out this problem.
- The 'score' command has been rewritten.  The old version is
available as 'oldscore'
- Saving throws have been rewritten.  They now work on a 25 point
scale (instead of 100) and they are not modified for level.  So
you'll have to wear saving throw eq if you want to make saves.
- Autoscan has been removed.  It will be unset when you log in
after reboot.  The "where" command is now allowed for mortals,
but will only show other players.
- It's been pointed out that high level players are getting quests
with low level characters and logging on their high levels to fetch
the items.  It has also been noted by me that people are weakening
mobs with high level characters and logging in their low levels to
finish them off.  Characters are intended to be independent of one
another.  This has prompted two changes.  The autoquest token items
are now nodrop.  Also, there has been an ammendment made to the
MULTIPLAYING policy that includes weakening mobs for your other characters.
- Fixed a memory leak in autoquest.  Also added an object flag for
autoquest.
- Fixed a couple more bugs in autoquest.  The code was returning when
it found someone who could begin questing again instead of continuing,
so hopefully it shouldn't skip ticks on people now.  Also there was a
bug in quest giveup, that's fixed.  If you gave up on a quest and now
get nothing when you type aquest time, go to Gortok and type aq fixme.
- Added some debug code to quests, also think I found why some people
would have a quest even though he said he didn't have one.
- The Elemental race has been renamed Angel.  I don't have any plans
to complete what I had planned for elemental, and the race doesn't
really make sense without it.
- Mob racial guessing code is back in.  That means most undead should
actually be flagged undead again.  Sunray should actually do damage
now.  Sorry this was disabled, not sure why.
- Crash bug in the new wear location code fixed.  Thanks Morgus for
finding this.
- I spent a great deal of time today putting in an autoquest system.
You will see an adventurers guild in Kore.  This is not open to the
public just yet, I need to do some more testing, but it will be ready
very soon.  You should find it quite challenging, as well as quite
interesting.
- I've heard a lot of confusion about why recall was changed.  The
reason it was changed was to clear the way for racial areas.  They're
not quite ready yet, but soon different races will start outside the
main city of Kore.  It has long been my intention to take the focus
off of the city of Kore as the center of the world and add some new
interesting cities.  This is a step in that direction.
- Bug in wild heal fixed.  Instead of just taking hitpoints if you
get unlucky it will hit you with poison damage.  It will not cause
you to be poisoned, just hit you with that damage type.
- Recall will now return you to the last room from which you entered
the game.
- Since you now have an abundance of moves, you can expect some new
things to cost movement.  This may mean melee takes moves, more if
you wield a heavy weapon.  It may also mean certain skills either
require you to have a certain number or percentage of moves, or will
take moves when used.  Expect this, don't be surprised if it comes.
- The remort gauntlet is going to be rewritten and you will be required
to pass it in order to remort, look for this in the coming weeks.
- You will now gain movement points based on dexterity when you level.
If you're already level 50 and you feel your moves are too low, you
can always remort.
- Dispel magic has been rewritten.  Each spell affect that is on the
victim will receive a saving throw.
- Area effect spells can now be cast without an argument as long as
there is a valid target present.
- Mobs that are immune to skills such as bash and block will no longer
report so, you will simply fail.  Also missing a skill will take the
same delay as succeeding.
- Group experience has been recoded somewhat.  See help EXPERIENCE.  Also
level restrictions on grouping have been removed. (You can thank Maerlyn
for this one, he chewed me out about group restrictions)
- You will no longer autoassist when not in the same room as the fighting
character.
- Death has been recoded.  You should stay in your group when you die and
pop up in the temple similar to an arena death, only your hps and mana will
be at 1, and your corpse will be where you died.
- The "visible" command will now dispel any remaining mirror images (Thanks
to Hagen for this suggestion)
- The affect portion of sunray is currently disabled while I decide how I
want to recode it.
- Stoneskin will no longer protect you from magical attacks, and it will now
tickle instead of miss, since missing was misleading.
- Stoneskin, Mirror Image, and safe rooms will no longer protect from poison
(Thanks to Hampo for pointing this out)
- Area effect spells will now hit all mirror images dispelling the spell
effect (Thanks Rufus for this suggestion)
- Some changes have been made to cursed items.  I suggest you treat cursed
items with a fair amount of respect.
- Cleaned up implementor-only system channel.
- Scavenger mobs will now wear the equipment they pick up.
- Bite will no longer take mana when your victim is not found. (Thanks to
Hagen for pointing this out)
- Some minor typos fixed
- Fly will now only reduce the number of movement points needed to move
from room to room, not nullify it completely.
- A bug has been fixed in enchant armor.  It should never have affected
wisdom.  The bug only affected some enchants, as there is a variation
in the affect of enchant armor.
- Warriors (and knights) will now do damage based on their level when
fighting without a weapon.
- Helpfiles on spells have all been recategorized, you now need to use
"help spell <spellname>" to access those helpfiles
- Locate object has been changed.  You may no longer locate objects on
mobs that are more than 10 level greater than your level.  The spell will
also always cast, whether it finds your target or not, whether the target
exists or failed due to your level.
- Clerics and thieves, you've asked for it for a long time, you got it.
Thieves will now receive 1 exp for each gold they steal from mobs that
are equal or greater than their level.  Clerics will now receive 1 exp
for each point of damage they heal on players other than themselves, and
only while that player is in combat.
- A lot of players level mages up to 15 or so in order to get locate
object.  To encourage the play of low level clerics, I have granted
clerics the locate spell at level 21.
- To compensate for the loss of wimpy to thieves, the delay on backstab
has been slightly reduced, and you may now backstab while stoneskinned.
- The spell 'blindness' is now considered a violent act.  Therefore it
may not be cast upon players, but may be cast while in combat.
- Following has been restricted.  You may only follow someone within 10
levels of you.
- The wimpy command has been removed.  Along with this change, the flee
command has been modified to make it a bit easier to flee, though it's
still based highly upon your dexterity.
- There is now a chance to ^Rfail fleeing^n from a fight.  This chance is
directly related to your ^YDexterity^n
- If you die and lose enough exp to put you below your previous level,
you will de-level. The exp loss cap has been greatly increased as
well. This won't affect lower levels, but higher level players will
lose a great deal more experience than previously.

See also: NEWS
#
"SPELL CHARM PERSON"

Usage       : cast 'charm person' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : (432/Itelligence points of person) hours

Is is not possible to charm anyone that is already charmed, if
you're charmed yourself, or if the person is higher level than
yourself. The person will get a saving throw versus "paralysation".

A charmed person will follow you, and not be able to attack you, you
can order charmed person using the order command.

See Also: FOLLOW, ORDER
#
"SPELL CAUSE CRITICAL"

Usage       : cast 'cause critical' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Cause critical is a more powerful version of cause serious.

See Also: CAUSE LIGHT, CAUSE SERIOUS 
#
"SPELL CAUSE LIGHT"

Usage       : cast 'cause light' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Cause light is a basic offensive spell for clerics where the caster focuses
harmful energy into his or her fists and attempt to strike the victim, causing
damage.  Since clerics are defensive in nature, the force of this harmful
energy isn't great.

See Also: CAUSE CRITICAL, CAUSE SERIOUS 
#
"SPELL CAUSE SERIOUS"

Usage       : cast 'cause serious' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Cause serious is a more powerful version of cause light.

See Also: CAUSE CRITICAL, CAUSE LIGHT 
#
"SPELL CHAIN LIGHTNING"

Usage       : cast 'chain lightning' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This *IMPRESSIVE* spell does a lightning bolt over an area affect, 
It is an extremely powerful spell, but it also tends to make a lot of
mobs angry. :)

See Also: LIGHTNING BOLT
