"SPELL COLOR SPRAY" "SPELL COLOUR SPRAY"

Usage       : cast 'color spray' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Save        : Versus spell for half damage.

This spell is more powerful than the chill touch spell.

See Also: CHILL TOUCH

For help on actual color, see: ANSI
#
COMBAT
These are commands that can be used while in combat:

CONSIDER What you always should do before even thinking of attacking
KILL     Basic command to initiate combat
FLEE     Makes you try to run away from combat
ASSIST   Joins in a battle of a person being attacked
TRACK    Follows the path to a mob
CAST     Casts an (offensive) spell
BATTLE   Takes you automatically to the PK arena

LINK     Information on freezing/losing link in battle

See also: PK, EXPERIENCE, DEATH, GROUP
#
COMMANDS

The COMMANDS command gives a canonical list of all the known verbs.

> commands

Each command listed should have help available by typing "HELP <command>".

See Also: HELP
#
COMM COMMUNICATING COMMUNICATION
These commands are used to communicate with several other characters at
once:

GOSSIP      Reaches everyone in the game
GRATS       Congratulates people in the mud. Reaches everyone
SHOUT       Reaches your nearby area
SAY         Reaches your whole room
LISTEN      Listen to mobs for useful information
CHAT        Chat with mobs for useful information
MUSIC       Sing a song or talk about music
GTELL       Group-tell, reaches only members of your group
EMOTE       Expresses your feelings
REPORT      Shows your statistics to your group
MAIL        For use at a postmaster, send mail to anyone in the game

TELL        Tell to any person in the world
WHISPER     Whisper to a person in your current room
SPEAK       Speak in the language of your race

SOCIALS     Shows a complete list of socials

See also: -
#
COMPACT

This command toggles the extra blank line output to your screen after each
command.  Useful if you have a small display.

See also: BRIEF
#
COMPARE

This command allows you to compare one weapon to another or one piece
of armor to another. It's pretty vague and just tells you if the average
dice damage (excluding possible damage bonuses) of one is greater than the 
other (in the case of weapons) or if the base armor value of one piece of
armor is better/worse/no different than another. Its a moderately useful
skill, but the spell "identify" is *FAR* superior.

See also: IDENTIFY, JUDGE
