"SPELL CONJURE ELEMENTAL"

Usage       : cast 'conjure elemental'
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell summons one of the elemental powers of air, earth, water or fire
to serve you.

See Also: -
#
CONSIDER

Usage : consider <victim>

Consider compares your offensive and defensive power vs the victim's power.
Your offensive power is simply your average damage with your weapons times
the number of attacks you get.  Your defensive power is your hit points 
(double power if you are sancted).  Consider makes a guess at how hard or
easy a mob might be for you to fight, but it just can't factor in everything!
Mages and clerics especially might finds mobs a lot easier or harder depending
on if they have mana for spells.

Results of consider, from easy to difficult:

Simple, extremely easy, really easy, easy, pretty easy, reasonably easy,
sort of easy, fairly easy, somewhat easy, even, somewhat hard, fairly hard,
sort of hard, reasonably hard, pretty hard, hard, really hard, extremely
hard, getting impossible, impossible, unthinkable.

See Also: -
#
CONSTITUTION

Constitution is a measure of how healthy a player is in a very general sense.
Constitution as an attribute modifies the amount of hit points a player can
get as a bonus when they level.

See Also: ATTRIBUTES
#
"SPELL CONTINUAL" "SPELL CONTINUAL LIGHT"

Usage : cast 'continual light'

This spell makes a temporary light source that can be help by the caster.

See Also: CREATE FOOD, CREATE WATER
#
"SPELL CONTROL WEATHER"

Usage       : cast 'control weather' ('better' | 'worse')
Accumulative: Yes
Duration    : -

This spell will change the "course" of the current weather.
Example:

> cast 'control wea' worse

See Also: -
#
CORPSE BODY

Corpses are from killed mobs or mortals.

See Also: DEATH
#
"SPELL CREATE FOOD"

Usage       : cast 'create food'
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell instantly creates an edible waybread. The delicious waybread 
will satisfy your hunger for 24 hours.

See Also: CONTINUAL LIGHT, CREATE WATER 
#
"SPELL CREATE SPRING"

Usage       : cast 'create spring'
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 10 turns

This spell creates a magical spring on the ground, providing clear water
to all for 10 turns before drying up.

See Also: CREATE WATER
#
"SPELL CREATE WATER"

Usage       : cast 'create water' <drink container>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Instantaneous

Expect disasterous results if cast upon a drink container which contains
another liquid than water. Empty or water containers will be filled
depending on the level of the caster.

Double amout of water will be created if it is raining (or worse).

See Also: CONTINUAL LIGHT, CREATE FOOD 
#
CRITICAL "CRITICAL_HIT" "CRITICAL HIT"

Over time and with practice, warriors develop the ability to use their
weapons with extreme skill.  At times they can find openings in the
defense of their opponent and attack a vulnerable location.  These
critical hits inflict a good deal more damage than a standard attack.

See Also: BLOCK, DISARM, RIPOSTE
#

"SPELL CURE BLIND"

Usage       : cast 'cure blind' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell will cure a person blinded by the "blindness" spell, it
can not remove blindness caused by for example cursed items.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL CURE CRITIC"

Usage       : cast 'cure critic' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell cures 5d8 + 3 + 1/4th the clerics level in hitpoints of damage.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL CURE LIGHT"

Usage       : cast 'cure light' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell cures 2d8 + 1 + 1/4th the clerics level in hitpoints of damage.

See Also: -
