"SPELL CURE SERIOUS"

Usage:      : cast 'cure serious' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell cures 3d8 + 5 + 1/4th the clerics level in hitpoints of damage.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL CURSE"

Usage       : cast 'curse' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Level based

Curse cast on a person that fails the saving throw, will reduce the
Damroll by one, and prevent the victim from recalling.

See Also: -
#
CUSTPROMPT

Usage: custprompt <prompt>

This command allows you to customize your Heroes of Kore Prompt (tm). You
can put any text you want in it, as well as the following codes:

$h: Current hit points	    $H: Maximum hit points
$m: Current mana            $M: Maximum mana
$v: Current movement        $V: Maximum movement
$g: Gold on hand            $b: Gold in the bank
$G: Total gold              $l: Current level
$x: Current experience      $X: Experience required for next level
$n: Your name               $$: A dollar sign
$f: Mob you are fighting    $c: Condition of the mob you are fighting
$a: Age                     $p: Current position (resting etc)
$R: Armor Class             $A: Alignment
$S: Strength                $D: Dexterity
$N: Constitution            $I: Intelligence
$W: Wisdom                  $C: Charisma
$t: Hitroll                 $d: Damroll

All the color codes as well as ^^\ (for new line) also work. Typing
'custprompt' without any parameters resets you to the default prompt.

See also: ANSI
#D
DAMAGE

The damage that you do is scaled.. each weapon type has a message and
the damage messages rise in increments of roughly 4 to 6 hit points per range.
It's not constant but after a while you can really tell how good or bad
a weapon is and how much damage it's doing by its damage messages. 

miss		scratch		graze		hit
injure		wound		maul		decimate
devastate	maim		MUTILATE	DISEMBOWEL
EVISCERATE	MASSACRE	DEMOLISH	ANNIHILATE
LIQUIFIES

See Also: -
#
DAMROLL

Your damroll is the amount of extra damage you do in addition to your 
weapon damage with each hit.  You can see your damroll when you type attr 
after 8th level.  It is added only to melee attacks.

See Also : HITROLL
#
DAWN DAY DUSK NIGHT

These times of day really dont have much affect on the game except that 
outdoor rooms at dusk and night are dark for those without a light or infra-
vision.

See Also: -
#
DEAF

(deaf) means that you don't hear shouts.  Toggle it with the noshout command.

See Also: FLAGS, NOSHOUT
#
DEATH DYING RIP

Death is something to be avoided at all costs.  When you die you are
brought back to life, but you lose a portion of your experience.  If
you lose too much experience, there is a chance you can lose a level.

See Also: -
