#
DEATHTRAP DT

Deathtraps are usually obvious traps that not only kill you, but also
destory all your equipment since they are unretrievable from the trap.
No reimburstments are given for deathtraps. Don't even ask. However,
you don't lose any experience for hitting a deathtrap.

However, people who claim they never DT are either liars, wimps, or
twinks.

See Also: TWINK
#
DEATHMATCH DEATHQUEST

Is a special mode in which the arena can be set by an immortal. When in
this mode a mortal doesn't lose experience when they die. Also when in
this mode a mortals don't actually die, they reappear in the temple
restored and a death is added to the totals

We try to run an "official" deathmatch each week.  Currently they are
held on saturday.  The winner of this deathmatch will be flagged as
the DQ Master for the week, and will also receive any item of their
choice to use until the following saturday.  There are additional
rules during these official deathmatches.  You may not follow other
players or group.  You may not recall yourself or others.  And as
always, you must listen and obey the immortal who is running the
quest.

* - You will no longer be dispelled before entering the arena, but
    you will be forced to follow yourself.

See Also: BATTLE, SCORES
#
DEFEND

Defend is a skill much like rescue only better! When you rescue someone,
you take the blows for them but the person you rescue stops fighting and
has to start all over again, losing valuable time and lost hits. Defend
lets the tank take the blows for someone (like rescue) but the person they
defend gets to keep fighting!! You must be wearing a shield in order to
defend successfully.

See Also: RESCUE
#
"SPELL DEFENSIVE HARMONY"

Usage       : cast 'defensive harmony'
Accumulative: Yes
Duration    : 24 hours

Defensive harmony grants the powers of armor to all members of caster's
group.

See Also: ARMOR, BARKSKIN
#
DESCRIPTION

Your description (settable on the connection menu) is what people see
when they look at you. They'll also see the equipment you wear, and if
they're a thief they might peek at your inventory.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL DETECT INVISIBILITY"

Usage       : cast 'detect invisibility'
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 5 hours per level

This spell enables you to see invisible items and players.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL DETECT MAGIC"
Usage       : cast 'detect magic'
Accumulative: No
Duration    : 5 hours per level

This spell will let you see the magical aura surrounding magical
objects.

See Also: -
#
DIAGNOSE

diagnose
diagnose <character>

The DIAGNOSE command tells you how wounded a character looks.  If you are
fighting someone, you can use DIAGNOSE with no arguments to diagnose the
person you're fighting.

> diagnose
> diagnose rasmussen

See Also: -
#
DISARM

Disarm forces the mob a warrior has engaged to unwield its weapon. Disarm is
especially valuable because mobs inflict less damage when they are bare-
handed. Disarm will initiate combat. This skill is ineffective against mobs
protected by Sanctuary.

>disarm
>disarm orc

See Also: BLOCK, RIPOSTE, CRITICAL HIT
#
"SPELL DISINTEGRATE"

Usage       : cast 'disintegrate' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Instantaneous

Disintegrate hits the victim with a massive wallop, hopefully making powder
of their body.

See Also: LIGHTNING BOLT 
#
"SPELL DISPEL MAGIC"

Usage       : cast 'dispel magic' <victim> 
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Dispel Magic neutralizes the effects, for good or ill, of spells cast by
mobs or other mortals.  Dispel Magic is ineffective against a mob's inherent
magical powers.

SEE ALSO: DISPEL SANCTUARY
#
"SPELL DISPEL EVIL"

Usage       : cast 'dispel evil' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Save        : Special

This spell will only affect evil creatures. An evil person of level
equal or less than caster will suffer 100 damage points.

If the victim is higher level than caster, the spell will inflict
(caster_level)d4 damage points, saving throw versus half damage.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL DISPEL GOOD"

Usage       : cast 'dispel good' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Save        : Special

This spell will only affect good creatures. An good person of level
equal or less than caster will suffer 100 damage points.

If the victim is higher level than caster, the spell will inflict
(caster_level)d4 damage points, saving throw versus half damage.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL DISPEL SANCTUARY"

Usage       : cast 'dispel sanctuary' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

This spell removes the sanctuary from characters only. Mobiles are unaffected
by this spell.

See Also: DISPEL MAGIC 
#
DISPLAY PROMPT

Modify your prompt to show your hit points, mana, movement points,
and/or mob condition.

> display off		Return to normal display
> display all		Display hit, mana, move points, and mob condition
> display color		Show the prompt in color; kinda neat, try it! :)
> display diagnose	Show the condition of the mob you are fighting.


The mob's condition only comes up when you are fighting. In those cases,
it gives you a description of its condition like: "excellent", "bruised",
"awful" - a very handy feature.

Play around with the command, it's pretty self explanitory and there are
*MANY* more options.

See also:  TOGGLE
#
DONATE

The Donate command removes an object you no longer want from your inventory
and deposits the item in the Donation Room west of the Temple Of Vulmarta
in Kore.  You can donate from any room in the game and there is no longer
any chance of the item getting junked.  Donating is an easy way to assist
new players.

Examples:

>donate longsword
>donate all.bread
>donate <number> coins

See Also: JUNK, SACRIFICE, BURY
#
