#
DUALWIELD "DUAL WIELD"
Warrior only

Warriors level 25 and higher gains the ability to wield a second weapon in
place of a shield.  The second weapon allows the warrior to have 50% more
attacks per round, but requires more strength to wield than the primary
weapon.

See Also: WARRIOR
#
DUERGAR "DARK DWARF"

Duergar are a race of dark dwarves, suited to living deep underground.  They
are inherently evil and shun surface dwellers.

See Also: RACE
#
DWARF DWARVES DWARVEN

Dwarves are a short-statured race who dwell in the mountains. They are a
strong and hearty race who loves the majestic primal beauty of the mountains
(also the gold, silver, and gems within). They have knowledge that time can
only bring since they are a long lived race. They are not very quick. Their
harsh enviroment gives them very little time for personal beauty. 

See Also: RACE
#E 
"SPELL EARTHQUAKE"
Usage       : cast 'earthquake'
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous
Save        : Versus spell for no damage 

This spell will damage everybody except the caster by
1d8+level_of_caster hitpoints.

See Also: -
#
EAT DRINK SIP TASTE FOOD HUNGER THIRST
If you're hungry or thirsty, these commands are for you!

> eat bread
> taste bread
> drink from cup
> sip fountain

See Also: CREATE FOOD, CREATE WATER
#
ANGELS

The angel embodies all that is holy.  These celestial beings are the agents of
the gods of good, sometimes entering the world of men to enforce their deity's
will.  They are rue to do this though as they surrender much of their power
upon entering the mortal plane.  The angel does, however, retain some of its
supernatural resistance to mortal magics.  They are also highly adept with both
weapon and spell, rendering these holy beings extremely potent adversaries.

See Also: REMORT, UNDEAD
#
ELF ELVES

Elves are a woodland race and are quick and intuitive.  They have a 
strong relationship with magic and are fierce when defending their homes 
and forests. They are graceful. However, strength and stamina are not their
main attributes.

See Also: RACE
#
EMAIL E-MAIL

If you supply a valid email address to Heroes of Kore, the immortals will
be able to verify your identity in case you should forget your password. You
can enter an email address via the main menu after you login. If you do not
supply an email address, the immortals WILL NOT be able to help you if you
forget your password.
If you lose your password email the mud from the email you have supplied to
kore@pro-usa.net

See Also: - PASSWORDS
# 
EMOTE :

Show people what you're feeling.  The shorthand is ":".

"emote <string>" will display your name, then the string.  For example,
if your name is "Quifael",

> emote is feeling very sad today.

will display:

