#
HIDE

Thieves Only.
When you type hide there is a chance that you hide in the room. If hidden
you can only be "sensed" by the "sense life" spell. Even if sensed your
identity will remain hidden. Hide is broken by pressing return, regardless
of wherther you typed a command or not.

Example:

> hide
Ok.
>  (you wait for ex. 5 mins and remain hidden for 5 mins)

>  (You pressed enter and no longer hide)

See Also: -
#
HITROLL

Your hitroll is you bonus chance to hit with each melee strike.  The 
hitroll is added to your roll to hit and then subtracts the opponent's AC 
to see if you are successful.

See Also : DAMROLL AC
#
"HIT POINT" HP

Hit point is a measurement of your current health.  When hit point reaches
zero, you die.  Fighters have excellent hit points; clerics, bards, and
thieves have fair hit points; and mages are weak in hit points.  Hit points
can be restored by sleeping, resting, or healing spells.  Warriors and
thieves have the quickheal skill which enhances healing.

See Also: MANA, MOVEMENT, DEATH, SLEEP, REST, HEAL, QUICKHEAL
#
HOBBIT 

Hobbits are a small race who love creature comforts. They love good food,
friends, and banter. They rather stay near their homes and live contently.
The rare adventurers are considered strange and somewhat pitied. Due to their
size and life style, they are not very strong, but however they are very
quick and nimble. They can see in the dark; they move gracefully and quietly.

See Also: RACE
