#
JUNK

Use JUNK instead of DROP if you want to keep the world a little cleaner.  If
you JUNK something, it will disappear and you'll get a few coins or experience
points, just as if you had dropped it in the dump.

donate <object>
donate <number> coins

> junk cup
> junk all.bronze
> junk 500 coins

See also: DROP, DONATE
#K
KEYS

Keys are used to lock doors, chests, and othersuchlike objects. Most of the
time the locks that the keys lock can be picked by a thief. Other times 
though, the lock is pickproof and only the key can open it. 
Keys are used to help keep areas behind doors more easily accessed by thieves,
sometimes though, it might be easier to steal a key from the inventory of a
mob. Other times, clever mobs will hold the key, or hold a bag with a key
in it (arg! you can't steal from held!)
Most keys are no-rent and have some sort of limit on the number allowed in
the game. If you can't find a key to an area, you might ask on the gossip
channel if someone has it. Chances are its out there... you might try
the spell 'locate object' to find the key too. Mostly, keys that open a 
locked door are found in the same zone the door they open is in. Unfortunately,
there's no way to tell, short of long experience on the mud, what door a 
given key opens.... you'll just have to try them all.

See also: THIEF, PICK, LOCKS, STEAL, LOCATE OBJECT
#
KICK

Fighters and Bards only.
The success of a kick depends upon how well you are learned. The higher
level you reach the harder you kick. There is one small catch -- whenever
you kick (or miss) you will be unable to type any command for three 
rounds of 'Violence' -- so be sure that you do not need to flee!

See Also: RESCUE, BASH
#
KILL HIT
