#
MOVEMENT MOVE MOVING
The following commands are used to travel around in the game:
N, NE, NW, E, S, SE, SW, W, U, D: Lets you move in that direction

LOOK     Essential for examining your surroundings
SCAN     For quickly looking into surrounding rooms
SEARCH   Search your room for hidden items

OPEN/CLOSE:  Opens a door or a container
LOCK/UNLOCK: Locks a door or a container. Requires a key
ENTER/LEAVE: Enter doors, portals, etc.

VIS      Become visible, cancelling effects of sneak, hide, invisbility
         etc.
EXITS    Shows you where the exits in the current room lead to
RENT     For use in the receptions of inns. When you re-enter, you will 
         start where you rented

STAND    Lets you wake up and stand up
REST     Lets you sit down; resting characters regenerate faster
SLEEP    Lets you sleep; you regenerate even faster, but have no vision
WAKE     Lets you wake up (or wake another character)

See also: -
#
MV

Movement measures your endurance in terms of the distance you can travel
before having to rest.  When movement reaches zero, you can no longer
move; if you are attacked without enough movement, you cannot flee.
Different terrains reduce movement points by different amount.  The spell
"Fly" enables the player to move at a reduced cost to movement points.

See Also: HIT POINT, MANA, FLEE, FLY
#
MULTIPLAYING

No multiplaying. You may have multiple characters here, but they are to
have no interaction with one another.  This includes dropping link with
one character to log in another character. This also includes using one
character to weaken a mob and logging in another character to kill it for
the exp or items.  The ONLY people allowed to use two characters at the
same time are Gods (level 58 and above). All others will be warned, dis-
connected, frozen, or sitebanned, depending on the circumstances.
#
MURDER

Kill command to hit another player.  To avoid accidental flagging (i.e.
trying to type "kiss redferne" but accidentally typing "kill redferne")
Note that it is illegal to kill other players.  If you try you will get
a KILLER flag.  If you are flagged as a killer, you are unable to do
damage and other players will be allowed to use the MURDER command to
kill you without being flagged themselves.

See also:  FLAGS, FORGIVE
#N
NAMES
When choosing a name, please try to choose one which is both medieval
and unique.  Good names help add to gameplay and will allow you to forge
an identity for yourself.  Simply put, your name should NOT be:

 - Nonsensical, unpronounceable or ridiculous.
 - Profane or derogatory as interpreted in any language.
 - Futuristic or common, such as 'Jill' or 'Laser'.
 - Similar to that of any Heroes of Kore Immortal, major mob, or equipment.
 - Significant in history, mythology, or any religion.
 - Comprised of various capital letters, such as 'BrACkkA' or 'CORTO'.
 - Comprised of ranks or titles, such as 'Lord' or 'Master'.
 - Composed of singular descriptive nouns, adverbs or adjectives,
   as in 'Heart', 'Big', 'Flying', 'Broken', 'Slick' or 'Tricky'.
 - Any of the above in reverse, i.e., writing Jade as 'Edaj'.
 - Any combination of singular descriptive nouns/adverbs or adjectives,
   as in 'Metaljacket Heartbound Earthstone or Softheart'.

If caught with a name similar to the one above, you will most likely have
your character frozen.  There is a reason we ask you when you first create
a character, and if you don't take the warning seriously, expect the
consequences.

See also:  POLICY
