NOSHOUT

NOSHOUT toggles whether or not you hear shouts.  (deaf) will appear after
your name in the WHO list.

See also: FLAGS, SHOUT, WHO
#
NOSUMMON
Due to problems we've had with players killing other players by summoning
them to Bad Places, all characters now have SUMMON PROTECTION turned on by
default.  This prevents people from summoning you and gives you a warning
message if someone tries.  If you want to let someone summon you (i.e. if
someone wants to summon you for a legitamate reason), type NOSUMMON to turn
off summon protection.  You can then type NOSUMMON again to turn protection
back on.

See Also: TOGGLE
#
NOTELL

Use NOTELL if you wish to prevent other players from using "tell" to
communicate with you.  (notell) will appear after your name in the WHO
list if you have notell on.

See Also: FLAGS, TELL, WHO, TOGGLE
#O
OBJECTS
Following commands are used to manipulate objects:

GET       Pick up something or take it out of a container
DROP      Drops an item
GIVE      Give gold or objects away
DONATE    Donates an item to the Temple Donation Room
JUNK      Recycle your items!
WEAR      Wear an item
HOLD      Hold an item. Wands and staves require holding to be used
REMOVE    Removes items from your person
SAC       Sacrifice a corpse on the ground

Using objects:

EAT/TASTE Eats some food
DRINK/SIP Drinks some liquid, preferrably not rotten
FILL      Fills a container with liquid
QUAFF     Drinks a magical potion
USE       Use a magical device
RECITE    Reads a magical scroll
POUR      Fills/empties liquid containers

Buying:

LIST     Shows what items a shopkeeper has for sale
VALUE    Makes the shopkeeper tell you what he'd give for an item
SELL     Sells an item to a shopkeeper. Not all shopkeepers buy anything.
BUY      Buys an item from a shopkeeper
AUCTION  Auctions an item off. Reaches everyone

See also: STAFFS, WANDS, SCROLLS, POTIONS
#
ORC ORCS

Orcs are a crude and vile race where only the strong survive and control the
weak. They are strong and hearty, but they are not so bright. They have
a particular hatred for elves and dwarves. They can see in the dark.

