"SPELL RELOCATE"

Usage       : cast 'relocate' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Will relocate the caster to the victim. It is essentially the opposite of
summon.

See Also: SUMMON
#
REMORT

Remorting is something that will be available only to high-level 
characters.  In order to be eligible for remort, a player must have
maxed out on exp.  They must then pass the remort gauntlet, which
will consist of a series of trials in a reserved area.

Remorting consists of being set back to level 1.  You may retain your
race and class, or choose a new race or class, so long as it is a valid
race/class combination.  Certain races are only open to remort.  These
are currently Thri-kreen, Undead, and Angels.

Also, if a character wishes to remort and retain their race and class, they 
can opt either for a random reroll, or to have three attribute points added
to their attributes.  No more than two points can be added to any one attribute
per remort.

Remort restrictions:
Undead may not be Bards or Druids

See Also: ANGEL, UNDEAD, THRI-KREEN
# 
REMOVE 

If you tire of wearing some armor or wielding a weapon.

> remove boots
> remove sword
> remove all
> remove all.bronze

See Also: WEAR, WIELD
