#
REPORT

This command sends a report of your current and max hp and mana to your
group.  You can use this command to let potential rescuers know how
low your hps are without forcing them to use the "group" command.  It is
designed as a convenience for groups with members who get lag or have slow
modems.

> report

See Also: GROUP, FOLLOW, GSAY
#
RESCUE

Fighters and Bards only.

This command is useful if you want to try and make an attacker hit you
instead of your poor friend who is being pummeled.  You can only 'turn'
one monster for each rescue attempt.  This is highly useful when playing
in groups, of course.

rescue <victim>

> rescue quifael

See Also: -
#
RETREAT

Retreat is a skill that allows a thief to find a path away from a monster 
without the monster noticing.  By doing this the character doesn't lose 
the normal exp for fleeing.

See Also: THIEF
#
RIPOSTE

In fencing a riposte is a skillful parry quickly followed with a counter-
thrust. Riposte blocks the mobs' attack and awards the player with an extra
attack of his own for one round of combat.

See Also: BLOCK, DISARM, CRITICAL HIT
#
ROLEPLAYING RP IN-CHARACTER IC

Roleplaying is not required on this mud, but it is something that is smiled
upon if you participate in it. Think of yourself as an actor when you're
roleplaying because that's what you are. You should try to get in the head
of your character when you're roleplaying - try to imagine what they would
do in your current situation, and then do that. Damn drows!

See Also: RACE, SPEAK
