#
STEAL

Thief Only.

Use steal to steal gold or items from people. The chance of not getting
caught depends on your skill.  If the person is asleep, steal always succeed.

Due to misuse of the steal command, it is now illegal to steal from other
players.  Doing so will get you a flag for your trouble.

Example:

> steal gold drunk

See Also: -
#
"SPELL STICKS TO SNAKES"

Usage       : cast 'sticks to snakes'
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Instantaneous

Summons a snake and makes it follow the caster.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL STONE SKIN" "SPELL STONESKIN"

Usage       : cast 'stoneskin' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Until last stony layer is destroyed

When stoneskin is cast, the victim gains layers of tough stony covering
on his/her/its skin (how many depends on the level of the caster).  Each
layer completely absorbs one combat hit before being destroyed.  Stoneskin
may be recast only when all layers are destroyed by hits or by time.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL STRENGTH"

Usage       : cast 'strength' <victim>
Accumulative: No
Duration    : Level hours

A person will gain 1 strength point from spell.  Maximum strength is 25. 

See Also: -
#
STUN "STUN TOUCH"

Thief only

Stun touch puts the victim in a stunned state for a moment, not allowing 
them to attack and taking more damage from physical attacks.  The victim 
is left unable to defend themself for a short time.  Stun touch delays
the thief for three rounds.

See Also: -
#
"SPELL SUMMON"

Usage       : cast 'summon' <victim>
Accumulative: -
Duration    : Instantaneous

Will summon a person of the name spoken. It is not possible to
summon someone of three or more levels above yourself.
If you attempt to summon a monster,it will get a saving throw.

See Also: RELOCATE, POLICY
#
"SPELL SUNRAY"

Usage        : cast 'sunray' <victim>
Accumulative : -
Duration     : Instantaneous

Sunray beams a ray of sunlight on the victim.  It is not intense enough to
hurt even a child, but rumors persist of situations where it is deadly...

See Also: -
