#
THIEF THIEVES
Thiefs are known to have very special qualities, that no other class offers.
They are deadly backstabbers, often sneaking in the killing blow before
the victim can react.  They know many dirty tricks in combat to confuse
their enemies.  They can pick locks that would frustrate the most powerful
of warriors.

Here is a list of your skills at level 50:

SPELLNAME		LEVEL	COST
scrounge		1	n/a
sneak			1	n/a
backstab		3	n/a
steal			5	n/a
pick lock		7	n/a
hide			9	n/a
palm			10	n/a
quickheal		10	n/a
scan			15	n/a
circle			20	n/a
stun touch		20	n/a
retreat			22	n/a
track			25	n/a
gauge			30	n/a
trip			35	n/a

See Also: CLASSES, SPELLS
#
THRIKREEN THRI-KREEN TRI-KEEN TRI-KREEN TRI

Thri-kreen are a mantis-like race who are not from this world. Their origin
has been lost over the ages; they don't even remember where they are from.
It has been speculated that they arrived here from some strange metal ship
that fell from the sky. Since they are not from this world, they do not
have the ability to cast magic spells. However, they are very strong, fast,
and hearty. They are not very intelligent or insightful due to their 
insect mentality. They have a particular fondness for elven flesh.

They can sense-life and they also have no need for sleeping or drinking. 
They are also capable of giving their victims venomous bites. Thri-kreen
are also immune to the "blindness" spell.

Thri-kreens are now available as a remort option, with extensive changes 
to their equipment slots.

See Also: RACE, REMORT
# 
TIME 

Gives you the current game time.  Your initial reaction to the
output of this command may be one of surprise, but you'll get used to it. 
You'll have to, at any rate, since certain things in the game depend on
this particular notion of time; the opening hours of the shops, for
example.

See Also: -
#
UPTIME

    Displays when the game was last booted and calculates how much time has 
passed since.

#
TITLES

Titles are set through a request to the imms. Players at or under level 20
have the generic titles. Players over level 20 may request that their title
be changed to a suitable one of their liking (not suitable: "wetted his bed
last night").
Mudmail Ayana with your request for a title. It must fit the mud and not be
stupid or offensive. No request for colors in titles. If your request does
not fit the mud, is stupid and or asks for colors, your request will not be
answered.

See Also: FLAGS
#
TOGGLES

TOGGLE shows you the current values of various toggles available on the MUD.
This command CAN NOT be used to change these values (see related commands.)
All of these toggles remain the same until you change them; i.e. they are
saved when you quit or rent.

See Also: DISPLAY, BRIEF, COMPACT, NOTELL, NOSHOUT, NOSUMMON, QUEST, REPEAT,
          WIMP, BATTLEBRIEF
#
TOKENS

Shiny quest tokens can be exchanged for rewards on the following scale:

15 - A pretitle
10 - An item rename certificate
8 - an amulet of Yari

Other prizes may be given out per specific quest at the perrogative of
the quest organizer.

Gold quest tokens are to be given to the gleeman for prizes.

See Also: QUEST
#
TRIVIA

Every now and then there will be trivia questions asked which you will 
receive a trivia point for, if you are the first to answer it right. 
You can save these points for prizes. 

40 - A bag full of potions
35 - A pretitle
30 - An item rename certificate
25 - An amulet of Yari
20 - Black Sash
15 - Shiny Quest Token
10 - Gold Quest Token
05 - An Karn ruin the mud t-shirt or an I love Ayana t-shirt or an
     I been downgraded button.

This is just one way a trivia quest may be handled. It will depend on
the immortal who is running the quest.

After you receive ten trivia points they can be turned in for one ten
points trivia point. To help the pack rats to keep their loads light.

^RThe Trivia Points are for the char that answers the question. They are
not to be given away to other chars. Anyone caught doing so will lose
all trivia points.^n

