See Also: NEWBIE
#U
UNDEAD

Undead are a race of magical creatures.  They include beings such as 
liches, ghouls, vampires, deathknights, and ghosts.  Their magical nature 
has made them resistant to magical attacks.  They are also often very 
intelligent and wise due to their age.  Undead are available only as a 
remort race. Undead beings have the power of gaze and bite. They must
drink blood either using bite or via some other source. They can also
see invisible objects.

See Also: DRAGON, KNIGHT, REMORT
#
UNGROUP

UNGROUP can be used by group leaders to disband the entire group, or
to kick a specific group member out of the group (and stop him/her from
following the leader).

> ungroup
> ungroup all
> ungroup loser

See Also: GROUP
#
USE WAND STAFF STAFFS WANDS

Use : Use <staff>
      Use <wand> <victim>

Using staff's will automatically target everybody (or everything) in a
room, execpt yourself. Therefore staff's are naturally very powerful, and
yet may be very dangerous to use around other players.

Using wands require that you point it at a target, which can be either a
character or an object.

Both staff's and wand's must be HELD in the hand prior to use! (Use the
grab or hold commands). You must still supply the name of the staff or
wand to avoid confusion.

See Also: -
#
UTILITY
These are commands designed to make the mud a better place:

TOGGLE     The top level command to view a lot of settings
COLOR      Color-code mud output
PROMPT     Changes your prompt
ALIAS      Create shortcuts for used commands
BUG        Report a bug that you know about
IDEA       Suggest any ideas have to improve the MUD
TYPO       Report a typo (be specific)
SAVE       Save your character
!          Repeats the last command you typed

See also: -
